title: JavaScript | MDN
readableText: MDN Web Docs JavaScript reference and guides. Covers language fundamentals, objects, async programming, modules, and browser APIs. Useful for quickly verifying syntax, standard library behavior, and best practices.

title: Learn React
readableText: The official React documentation for learning components, state, effects, rendering patterns, and how to think in React. Includes practical examples and common pitfalls.

title: Vite Guide
readableText: Vite documentation covering dev server, build pipeline, environment variables, plugins, and configuration. Helpful when setting up fast local development for modern web apps.

title: Firebase Authentication Documentation
readableText: Firebase Auth docs for enabling sign-in methods, integrating with web apps, handling auth state changes, and securing routes. Includes troubleshooting for common errors like auth/operation-not-allowed.

title: Tailwind CSS Documentation
readableText: Tailwind CSS docs for utility classes, layout, typography, responsive design, and theming. Great for building consistent UI quickly without custom CSS.

title: World News | The Guardian
readableText: A world news page covering current events. Useful for testing news-category clustering and verifying that semantic search finds content by topic.

title: Allrecipes | Food, friends, and recipe inspiration
readableText: Recipe home page with cooking ideas and popular dishes. Useful to validate the food/recipes category, and for testing memory snippets and keyword extraction.

title: Booking.com | Official site
readableText: Travel booking site for hotels and stays. Useful for testing the travel category and for evaluating semantic queries like 'cheap hotel in tokyo'.

title: Amazon.com. Spend less. Smile more.
readableText: Ecommerce marketplace. Useful for shopping category clustering and testing searches like 'wireless headphones under 100'.

title: Jobs | LinkedIn
readableText: Job search listings and filters. Useful for testing the jobs category and validating queries like 'frontend engineer roles' even without exact matches.

title: Nutrition | Healthline
readableText: Health and nutrition articles. Useful for health category clustering and semantic searches like 'healthy recipes' and 'protein intake'.

title: GitHub: Where the world builds software
readableText: GitHub landing page for repositories, issues, and pull requests. Useful for developer workflow memories and testing semantic queries about code and repos.
